(vi) Effect of development on the area due to change of use or intensity of use; and
(v) Possibility of multiple use.;

(i) Effects on surface and ground water quality and quantity;
(ii) Effects on the flow regime of the water course;
(iii) Effect on downstream uses and users;
(iv) Effect on riverine ecosystems; and
(v) Effect on siltation patterns of water bodies.;

(i) Baseline air quality;
(ii) Effects on the ambient air quality, such as smog formation, cumulative effect of
emissions, type of particulate matter;
(iii) Types and estimated amount of air pollutants;
(iv) Effects on human health, crops, wildlife, livestock and other organisms; and
(v) Effects on built environment.
